         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ Mr. Bentham seems to have not known that Bamboos are recorded from at least three or four localities in Australia. ¶  Carron found one in Kennedy's sad expedition, and narrates it in his diary. ¶  ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.03.00b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To the Gardeners' Chronicle</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from 'Home correspondence. Bamboos in Australia'. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Gardeners' chronicle</seg>, 4 May 1878, p. 569 (B78.05.01). The letter is dated to March as the latest likely date that it could have been sent to be included in this issue.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr. Bentham seems to have not known that Bamboos are recorded from at least three or four localities in Australia.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Bentham (1863-78), vol. 7, p. 459, where he wrote 'Of the conspicuous tribe <name key="Bambusaceae">Bambusaceae</name>, so generally spread over the tropical regions of the New as well as the Old World, no representative has as yet been detected in Australia'. See also M to G. Bentham, 12 January 1878.</p>
               </note> Carron found one in Kennedy's sad expedition, and narrates it in his diary.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. MacGillivray (1852), vol. 2, pp. 124-5.</p>
               </note> Another is known 80 miles up the Adelaide River.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B67.12.01, p. 86.</p>
               </note> Another, again, in the back country of Nichol Bay, and one from beyond Camden Harbour.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No published reference up to 1878 to the genus being near Nichol Bay or Camden Harbour (both WA) has been found.</p>
               </note> I have been unsuccessful hitherto to get from the settlers in or near any of these districts flowers of these <name key="Bambusaceae">Bambusaceae</name>.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-style: italic; "
               xml:lang="en">F. Von Müller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Bambusaceae">Bambusaceae</name>
            </p>
         </div>
